All Classes

Class
Description
AbstractMenuItem
The base class for all menu related classes MenuBundle, MenuLeaf.
Category
The category class is used in restaurant menu to represent each category in the menu.
InputHandler
The input wrapper class for input exceptions.
MenuBundle
The MenuBundle class is a subclass of AbstractMenuItem class which represents a promotional items sold in bundle.
MenuItem
The MenuItem interface defines a set of methods to accesss the menu related classes i.e.MenuBundle and MenuLeaf.
MenuLeaf
The MenuLeaf class is a subclass of AbstractMenuItem class which represents individual alacarte item.
MenuList
The MenuList interface defines a set of methods to accesss the classes which contain multiple menu items.
Order
The Order class is a record of a collection of menu items made by customers.
Reservation
The Reservation class represents a reservation for a specified table and time.
Restaurant
Restaurant class connects different systems in the restaurant.
RestaurantApp
Main application entry point
SalesReport
Sales report class for a given time period.
Staff
Restaurant staff information class.
TableManager
Manages table and reservation in the restaurant.
